caption: Love this place! Good drinks, friendly staff. Highly recommend the crabcake sandwich.
wonderful seafood in a beautifully decorated environment. a true gem!
Cute hole in the wall, tasty food, n super friendly staff
Wonderful NJ shore style seafood and great drinks. You can reserve the outside patio on Resy!
The fried shrimp 🍤 is bomb!!
Drinks were Bomb...
Great fun! Food was fantastic!
the waiters were hot and i brought one home wit me
Food was great
Great burger with Taylor pork roll.
Friendly staff and tasty food!
Food was not very good. Service was great. After over cooking my fish,  they agreed I did not have to pay for the food. Will go back and have drinks.
Ray is AMAZING
Loved the atmosphere
Had some rub that tasted like maple syrup, it was like eating a pancake.

This place is incredible! Super fun casual place but in the best way which feels like you walked into a friends joint. Service was so friendly and a real treat to sit at the bar with great food and drinks. Thursday specials were on point - with $3.99 fish tacos and then $14 for a half dozen oysters and cava - the best! Highly recommend checking this place out and stopping by for a quick drink or a great meal.
Awesome service and great quality food
Answer the phone guys. Some of us still wanna patronize even when we r at work. Lol. Nobody ever answers the phone ☹️. Calling in my order would help so much... FIX THE PHONE  PLEASE LOL.
Fun. Funky. Tasty. Great vibe.

Came here and was looking forward to trying the boardwalk chicken. Sat at the bar and waited and waited.  Then, apparently a regular came and sat next me and immediately received a drink. The bartender almost walked away, but realized maybe he should offer service? I asked for a menu and he handed it to me and said they had everything.  I tried to order a vodka pineapple, but apparently they don't have pineapple juice :/.  I briefly looked over the menu and decided to try a drink on special and the boardwalk chicken.  But I waited... and waited... and waited.  I ended up leaving and going to a different establishment in AdMo.  It wasn't even that busy, but apparently the bartender just didn't want my business.
Loved our time at Pop's. Great fresh oysters in a laid back environment surrounded by the friendliest of people.  Outdoor patio a bonus on a beautiful day.

Fantastic little bar with a super likeable and fun bartender. We tried their Grapefruit drink and had some calamari and fried pickles along with it. All was freshly done and tasted delicious. Got to know something new, the Dickel pickle, worth a try...
Customer service is everything!! Will definitely be back!
Good food and drink in a casual setting. Loved the fried oyster sandwich. The retro games in the back were a lot of fun too.
Great oysters, nice service.
Great place for fresh oysters, fried sea food, and beer. Staff are great and music is good
Saw a bug
Easy access oysters, friendly bar tenders, better than expected brunch. Hard to beat.
Perfectly fine bar for a mid afternoon drink

This place is such a gem. I've been coming here for years, never once been let down. tonight was with a first date, and it was perfect, very low key, very quiet, great atmosphere, superb food. Still my favorite bar.
Decent food, fairly cheap for the area. Not great service from bartender

Casual beach bar atmosphere.  Good selection of beer.  Sticking with the beach atmosphere, some beers are served in a can with a coozie.  The menu has some tasty offerings.  I recommend 2 items from the menu... Smelt (a small, light fish, slightly larger than an anchovie) served fried.  The only place that I know that serves smelt. Very tasty.  Also, if you're a hot dog fan, you MUST order a hot dog here; you'll thank me later.
Just a great place to have some eats in the neighborhood. Plenty of TV's to catch a game. Great chowder. Price point is good $$

We stopped in after a day at the zoo and we were not disappointed. The fried oysters were delish! We also enjoyed fried calamari and the peel and eat shrimp, all over some well priced and well poured cocktails. I recommend stopping through if you're in the area and up for a quick bite.
Beware, this place could be out of bacon!! The burger was pretty good tho
Fun relaxed boardwalk like seafood joint. The orange crushes are solid and so is all the food.
Hamburger was good.  Chilli, meh.
Great, friendly service. Best oyster happy hour in town.
Nice and friendly neighborhood bar with good seafood (their fried calamari are fantastic and their crabcake is great).
Good service and a better than pub seafood menu.
Dive beach bar in Adams Morgan. Favorites include: Pop's Patty with Taylor roll, and smelts, and the peel n eat shrimp. $1 oysters. Local brews. Pinball and arcade games upstairs!
HH=$1 oysters!
Good place to pop into for a beer and some catfish tacos.
Insanely overpriced. Poor quality
Fried seafood and some beer in a pretty good recreation of a seaside dive restaurant.
Cheap oysters, beer, and great service. The nighborhood is overall an amazing area. Pops is definitely one of the local hot spots for this neighborhood. Again, cheap oysters and beer...enough said.

Being allergic to shellfish there was surprisingly a lot I could eat here. The hamburger was very good. My fiancé ordered the crab legs and loved them. The atmosphere takes you to a beach which is great. Food came fast too.
Watched the caps game with some awesome folks and oysters are the best in DMV. Bartender very nice.

Now this was a random but awesome find.  Doesn't look like much from the outside but inside is a good bar area with seating upstairs.  Had the Old Bay beer battered fried blue catfish sandwich.  It was absolutely delicious!  My wife had the simple catfish platter which was also good but failed to compare.  The Pop's Original Orange Crush was also spot on.  Upstairs has several video games and some pinball machines.  Had a blast playing those while we waited for our food.  Just wish I had more time but we were trying to beat a storm rolling in.  Service was also fantastic and the bartender was super friendly.  I will definitely be back.
Great oysters and gumbo!
Bartender was rude. Took 30 minutes to get half dozen oysters

Extremely small with good atmosphere, however the staff wasn't very friendly. Also the menu is small, with mostly fried options. (I struggled to find anything that wasn't fried). They offer a oysters & clams "bar", which seemed to be a waste of money.
Great foo, great service.
Nice place. Arcade game upstairs. Prices are a bit on the pricey side taking into account the portions.
Great place to get fresh seafood, people are friendly and will offer a great service.
Great food. Great service.
The bartender was a bit of a jerk to my friend.  Warmed up a bit later after we spent more money.  Fish tacos we're good though.
It's a dive bar with oysters. It's awesome. Great vibe.
$1 oyster happy hour 5-7pm

If you are looking for a super friendly seafood bar, this is your place. The bartender is great, so helpful. The service is, as I said, friendly. And the food, super tasty and delicious. I had the crab cake sandwich, with fries and coleslaw (one of the best I've ever had). Definitely a wonderful spot.
It was nice
Friendly and great mezcal bloody marys
Very good blue catfish, eat the invasive species harming Chesapeake Bay
Not that cheap but truly tasty. Worth it.
Great catfish and oysters
I know this is a seafood location, but The pork roll burger is amazing and worth diverging from a fish pick. However fried smelts are pretty great too.
Pork bun burger is step number one when visiting here for the first time.

Super fun atmosphere, and a great selection of oysters.  Other food is mostly boardwalk fare, and it’s not exactly a great place to have a full lunch or dinner. But as far as snacks with your beer goes, they’ve got you covered.  Oh, and champagne on tap!

Fun bar, nice atmosphere, kitschy without being too over the top. Cheap beers are nice, the crushes are great, and the food's solid, too. Never quite know whether to come here for dinner, drinks, etc. as the menu is a little eclectic -- nothing ever jumps out to me on it. A favorite bar in the neighborhood nevertheless!

When you want to get away from the hustle and bustle of the city and feel like you're back on the boardwalk, inside a beachfront restaurant.... then Pop's SeaBar my friends is a lovely escape. The combination of awesome food, a casual and relaxed environment with fantastic service makes this an amazing place. Eat, hang out and just have fun enjoying the awesome atmosphere.  The owners and staff are simply wonderful people...They are so friendly and courteous, it makes you feel as if you are long lost friends :-)  ( and that is rare to find ). If you're in DC do not miss out on visiting this place!! It would be a shame if you did!  :-)
Great for oysters!
Awesome seafood spot! The decor makes you feel like you're at the beach and the service is top rate. Try the Happy Oysters, you won't be disappointed!!
Great bar service in a fun atmosphere. Can't go wrong here!
The service was extremely slow and the cook kept wiping his butt every 10 seconds and then was touching food without gloves.  First time and last time patron !
Comfy & tasty.
Friendly team. Took about 30 minutes for the raw oysters, but they were worth the wait.
Great vibe at this low key bar. French fries and oysters with a beer in a coosie. Do it.
I almost don't want to rate them highly because they are definitely a hidden gem for locals. So just pretend you never saw this
Food quality and portions are decreasing while the price is staying the same. Not what it used to be.
Place is dope, great food, good times. Dustin is the best, come here if you want some great laughs and good drink.
Great atmosphere and food!!
Great place! Casual with good food and cocktails

Loved this spot!! Chef and bar tender have awesome back stories and are insanely friendly
Great good and drinks, and STAFF!
Nice view by the window
Terrific low key place with good beers and smelts. The beer prices are a little steep but not if you get there for happy hour. The fried chicken is also really good.
Relaxed place to people watch, get laid back food and cold brews. The missus loves it here
Good

Stopped in after a concert. Joy, a new bar tender was fabulous.  She was great at making a lemon drop Martini, even though she had never done it before. She improvised nicely. She was fun, friendly, and about focused on phenomenal customer service even though she was by herself. It got a bit busy but she continued to provide excellent service.  Less salt on the fries and it would have been perfect!
Crab cake was really delicious, and price also reseanable.

This is my new favorite local casual haunt. The sour highballs are so refreshing, and I have never craved a fish sandwich until this place came into town. The menu is limited but that's part of the appeal---simplicity!
Pork Roll!!! A welcomed sight for this Jersey guy. I asked for just a nice big pork roll sandwich which they happily agreed to do. It was delightful.

Pops is a nice addition to Adams Morgan. You may have read about the ice cream sandwich luge shot, and that's why I went. Who doesn't love ice cream sandwiches? As much as I wanted to love this combination drink-snack, it was actually just really messy and sticky, and hard to execute. I would like to go back and try some of their food b

Casual bar with Jersey Shore boardwalk seafood menu. Nice staff and fun themed decor. Boardwalk chicken is basically tasty chicken bites.  Nice selection of fish sammies and fresh oysters. Lightly fried smelts which I grew up on, could have used some seasoning though. And Ice Cream Waffle sandwiches! Simple cocktails and limited beers on draft (basic can selection). Liked the staff. I'm coming back
One of the happiest and brightest places on the block; and the hotdog is AMAZINGLY and simply spectacular!
